go-av1 — pure-Go AV1 video decoder.

This is an original Go implementation of the AV1 decoding process, written from
the public AV1 Bitstream & Decoding Process Specification (Alliance for Open
Media) and informed for cross-checking by the BSD-2-Clause reference decoders
dav1d (https://code.videolan.org/videolan/dav1d, © VideoLAN and dav1d authors)
and libaom (https://aomedia.googlesource.com/aom, © The Alliance for Open Media).

AV1 is an open, royalty-free codec (royalty-free patent grant by AOMedia,
designed patent-free). No proprietary source or disassembly was used.

Reference material:
  - AV1 Bitstream & Decoding Process Specification (public, AOMedia).
  - dav1d, libaom (BSD-2-Clause) — used only as behavioural references for
    bit-exact cross-checking of intermediate values, not copied.
